## Constraints

### MUST:
- Express every state change as an event with semantic meaning
- Make every command and event handler idempotent
- Keep write and read models separate — never query from a command handler against the projection
- Version events explicitly when their schema evolves
- Persist events before publishing them (transactional outbox or equivalent)
- {{MUST_RULES}}

### MUST NOT:
- Mutate persisted events (events are immutable)
- Mix command and query in the same handler
- Make sagas synchronous wait-points — they are reactive coordinators, not RPC chains
- Couple projections to the write model — they consume events, not aggregates
- Skip idempotency for "guaranteed once" delivery — there is no such guarantee
- {{MUST_NOT_RULES}}

